It often helps to convert improper fractions to mixed numbers, because then we can compare first the integers, then the remaining fractions.

$\begin{align}
-\dfrac{5}{2}&=-2\dfrac{1}{2}\\\\
-\dfrac{7}{3}&=-2\dfrac{1}{3}
\end{align}$

The integer parts of $-2\dfrac{1}{2}$ and $-2\dfrac{1}{3}$ are the same, but the fractions are different. $\dfrac{1}{3}$ has the same numerator, but a larger denominator than $\dfrac{1}{2}$. So $-2\dfrac{1}{3}$ is *closer to* $0$ than $-2\dfrac{1}{2}$ is. Even though $0$ does not appear on the number line, it is to the right of any negative number. That means $-\dfrac{7}{3}$ is point $\greenD{c}$.
